    "modeling non-rigid or deformable geometry, for example a human, is a classical problem for graphics research.",
    "This topic is well aligned with research on dynamic NeRFs and broadens human-centered computer vision research to the 3-D case.",
    "Similarly to the prior subsection, the two general problem formulations are multi-view and monocular scenes, which we use to distinguish current research objectives.",
    "We can additionally differentiate work by it's reliance on generalizing humans and their poses.",
    "HumanNeRF (Zhao et al. 2022) exemplifies both of these points as a method that focuses on the multi-view paradigm while generating generalizable human poses."
